                    <h1>About Me</h1>
                    <p>Hi, I'm Eduardo Amaral. I'm a videogame designer with a strong academic focus on level design and narrative design. I recently graduated with a Master's degree in Videogame Design, following a Bachelor's degree in Multimedia Design and a specialized high school diploma in Computer Science.</p>
                    <p>I'm especially drawn to the relationship between environment, storytelling, and player behavior — how level structure, visual cues, and narrative context can guide players without breaking immersion. Whether designing a level or shaping narrative flow, I aim to create experiences that feel intentional and cohesive.</p>
                    <p>Alongside game development, I have an academic background in front-end web and web design, with an emphasis on layout, usability, and visual coherence rather than heavy programming. This has shaped how I think about interfaces, clarity, and user experience across interactive projects.</p>
                    <p>As an early-career designer, I'm motivated by learning, iteration, and collaboration, and I'm eager to continue developing my skills through hands-on projects and meaningful creative challenges.</p>

